'''学校法人神戸中华同文学校'''（{{jpn|j=神戸中華同文学校|hg=こうべちゅうかどうぶんがっこう|rm=Kōbe Chūka Dōbun Gakkō}}；[[英語|英語]]譯名：{{lang|en|Kobe Chinese School}}）是[[日本|日本]][[兵庫縣|兵庫縣]][[神户市|神户市]][[中央区_(神户市)|中央区]]的中国大陆国际学校。这是五个日本的[[中华学校|中华学校]]之一，和两个日本的中国大陆国际学校之一<ref name=Japantimes>Co, Emily. "[http://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2008/12/23/issues/school-bridges-china-japan-gap/#.VPvVqOG56VA School bridges China-Japan gap]" ([http://www.webcitation.org/6Wrqi4lA6 Archive]). [[日本時報|日本時報]]. December 23, 2008. Modified January 30, 2015. Retrieved on March 8, 2015.</ref>。除了日語及英語課，大部份課程皆以[[漢語|漢語]]教學，並採用[[簡體中文|簡體中文]]。 

{{transh}}
It provides elementary and junior high school education in grades 1-9<ref>"[http://www.city.osaka.lg.jp/contents/wdu010/digitalbook/enjoy/eigo/index.html#page=91 A Guide for Living in Osaka Enjoy Osaka] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302084532/http://www.city.osaka.lg.jp/contents/wdu010/digitalbook/enjoy/eigo/index.html |date=2016-03-02 }}." City of Osaka. p. 91.</ref> and offers first choice in admission to children of alumni. The second choice is priority to Chinese people. The school established a policy of trying to minimize enrollment of Japanese students in 2000.<ref name=Fujikata>Fujikata, Satoru. "[http://ajw.asahi.com/article/behind_news/social_affairs/AJ201108298173 Japanese parents see value of Chinese, Indian schools] " ([https://www.webcitation.org/6WrvmY3MT?url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/behind_news/social_affairs/AJ201108298173 Archive]). ''[[Asahi_Shimbun|Asahi Shimbun]]''. August 30, 2011. Retrieved on March 8, 2015.</ref> In 2008 about 40% of the students were Japanese nationals who are ethnic Chinese.<ref name=Gottliebp102>Gottlieb, Nanette. "Japan: Language Planning and Policy in Transition." In: Kaplan, Robert B. and Richard B. Baldauf. ''Language Planning and Policy in Asia: Japan, Nepal, Taiwan and Chinese characters'' (Language planning and policy). [[Multilingual_Matters|Multilingual Matters]], 2008. ISBN 1847690955, 9781847690951. Start: [https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA102 102] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA102 |date=20160404142946 }}. CITED: p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA133 133] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA133 |date=20200729112751 }}.</ref>
{{transf}}

==学生人口==
2008年40%的神戸中华同文学校学生们是日本公民华人。<ref name=Gottliebp102>Gottlieb, Nanette. "Japan: Language Planning and Policy in Transition." In: Kaplan, Robert B. and Richard B. Baldauf. ''Language Planning and Policy in Asia: Japan, Nepal, Taiwan and Chinese characters'' (Language planning and policy). [[Multilingual_Matters|Multilingual Matters]], 2008. ISBN 1847690955, 9781847690951. Start: [https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA102 102]. CITED: p. [https://books.google.com/books?id=dboOAtK3Nv4C&pg=PA133 133].</ref>

